@page "/"

<PageTitle>Prisoner's Dilemma</PageTitle>

<section class="hero-panel">
    <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">A game about trust under pressure</p>
        <h2>See how cooperation survives, fails, and returns in repeated rounds.</h2>
        <p>
            Prisoner's Dilemma is a strategy game where each choice changes the next one.
            Play against AI, watch two strategies face off, or compare every strategy in a tournament.
        </p>

        <div class="strategy-tags">
            <span class="tag">Player vs AI</span>
            <span class="tag">Simulation</span>
            <span class="tag">Tournament</span>
            <span class="tag">Strategy Library</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-figure">
        <div>
            <p class="matrix-label">Core rule</p>
            <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem;">One betrayal can reshape the whole match.</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">
                The payoff matrix rewards short-term gain, but repeated play rewards memory,
                retaliation, forgiveness, and pattern recognition.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="round-strip" aria-label="Example round history">
            <span class="round-token cooperate">C</span>
            <span class="round-token cooperate">C</span>
            <span class="round-token betray">D</span>
            <span class="round-token cooperate">C</span>
            <span class="round-token betray">D</span>
            <span class="round-token betray">D</span>
            <span class="round-token cooperate">C</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="summary-grid">
    <article class="score-card">
        <span class="label">Play</span>
        <span class="value">Round by round</span>
        <p>Choose cooperate or betray and watch the score change immediately.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="score-card">
        <span class="label">Watch</span>
        <span class="value">Strategy vs strategy</span>
        <p>See how memory-based and opportunistic strategies perform against each other.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="score-card">
        <span class="label">Rank</span>
        <span class="value">Tournament table</span>
        <p>Run a round-robin tournament and compare total score, wins, and cooperation rate.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="score-card">
        <span class="label">Study</span>
        <span class="value">Strategy library</span>
        <p>Review the behavior, temperament, and difficulty of each strategy.</p>
    </article>
</section>

<section class="panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Where to begin</p>
    <div class="control-grid">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="play">Play vs AI</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline-light" href="simulation">Watch simulation</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline-light" href="tournament">Run tournament</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline-light" href="strategies">Browse strategies</a>
    </div>
</section>
